In your `updateMessage(message)` method, can you try:

```
updateMessage(message) {
    let { messages } = this.state;
    messages.push(message)
    this.setState({ messages })
}
```

From your code:

    updateMessage(message) {
      this.state.messages.push(message);
    }

You&#39;re modifying the state directly and [you&#39;re not supposed to do that](https://reactjs.org/docs/state-and-lifecycle.html#do-not-modify-state-directly) (except for in the constructor). It won&#39;t cause a re-render in this way. Instead, clone the state, modify it, then update the state via [`setState`](https://reactjs.org/docs/react-component.html#setstate). Calling `setState` will invoke a re-render.

    updateMessage(message) {
      this.setState({
        messages: [...this.state.messages, message],
      });
    }

**Your error is in this part**

    updateMessage(message) {
        this.state.messages.push(message);
      }
**You can not change state directly. You must use setState() method to change state**

    updateMessage(message) {
            this.setState({
                 messages : [...this.state.messages, message]
            });
          }

